CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 5, 1945, pg. 9 reads: "Named to the national Board of the YWCA Nominating Committee recently was Mrs. Lucille Cuthbert, wife of the eminent Dr. William Cuthbert, whose activities in Y have borne good fruit. Mrs. Cuthbert, modest and retiring, is the first Pittsburgh colored woman to be so named. - Courier Photo by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Lucille Cuthbert seated in leaf patterned armchair, in interior with glass paned door in background
